main event: A bright, flashing object was observed over Crystal Lake, Michigan for about 10 minutes by a 14-year-old girl.
interesting points: The object made a loud roar with a predominant note at around 600 cps, and brightly illuminated the front yard of the cottage where the witness was staying.
The object disappeared and then reappeared, flying over the lake and continuing until it was out of sight.
The witness found it difficult to get details about the object due to the brightness of the light.
The investigation concluded that the sighting was likely caused by an infrared photo mission, and that other sightings in the area were attributed to normal aircraft and astronomical observations.
The project investigated various reports in the Lansing, Michigan area, including sightings of meteors, the planet Venus, and reflections on fog.
